results.name: PG 5 'Bred'
results.story: The Nike PG 5 ‘Bred’ treats Paul George’s fifth signature shoe with an essential color palette rooted in the brand’s history in basketball. Black mesh and leather are utilized on the low-profile upper, accented with contrasting scarlet hits of color throughout. In lieu of a traditional Phylon midsole, the sneaker’s cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Air unit stitched directly to the upper. Underfoot, a red rubber outsole features a multidirectional tread for maximum grip.

results.name: Wmns Flex Experience Run 10 'Venice Crimson Bliss'
results.story: Designed for the casual runner, the Nike women’s Flex Experience Run 10 ‘Venice Crimson Bliss’ highlights delicate hues on a breathable mesh upper with supportive no-sew overlays and textile quarter panels marked with embroidered Swoosh branding. The lightweight build is placed atop a Nike Flex sole unit, featuring a series of cuts underfoot that promote the natural motion of the foot, ultimately yielding a smooth and comfortable ride.

results.name: Wmns Revolution 5 FlyEase 'Summit White Crimson Bliss'
results.story: The Nike women’s Revolution 5 FlyEase ‘Summit White Crimson Bliss’ bundles stretchy comfort and buoyant cushioning in a pastel-hued package. The pale green knit upper is secured with no-tie elastic laces and an adjustable hook-loop-strap, while zippered closure wraps around the back of the collar and allows the shoe to be easily slipped on and off. The sneaker rides on a full-length foam midsole with textured sidewalls designed to reduce overall weight. Reliable traction is provided by a rubber outsole, spaced to allow the foot to flex naturally.

results.name: LeBron 18 TD 'Soundwave'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 TD ‘Soundwave’ offers a scaled-down version of LeBron James’ signature shoe for little feet. This music-themed edition features mismatched Volt and Bright Crimson accents between the left and right shoe. Both utilize black knit textile on the upper, secured with a combination of elastic no-tie laces and a detachable tongue with hook-and-loop closure. Atop the tongue, a playful graphic displays a crowned cartoon lion wearing headphones.

results.name: LeBron 18 PS 'Soundwave'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Nike LeBron 18 PS ‘Soundwave’ delivers a music-themed take on LeBron James’ signature shoe. Mismatched color blocking distinguishes the pair, featuring neon Volt accents on the left shoe and Bright Crimson on the right. Both shoes carry a black textile knit upper with matching black foam midsoles. Atop the tongue, a playful graphic depicts a cartoon lion wearing a crown and headphones. A volume dial graphic adorns the custom sockliner.

results.name: Nike Air Presto Sunrise Sunset
results.story: The Nike Air Presto ‘Sunrise’ brings back a gradient CO.JP colorway that originally released in 2001 exclusively to the Japanese market. The yellow-to-violet color scheme accompanies a comfortable build originally described as a T-shirt for feet. A semi-translucent TPU cage adds lightweight structure to an upper made with spacer mesh, a breathable material that offers stretch in every direction. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a Phylon midsole with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning.  Size Guide: XXS = US M's 3-5 & W's 4.5-6.5 | XS = US M's 5-7 & W's 6.5-8.5 | S = US M's 7-9 & W's 8.5-10.5 | M = US M's 9-11 & W's 10.5-12.5 | L = US M's 11-13 | XL = US M's 13-15

results.name: Nike Air Max 95 Kim Jones Black Total Orange
results.story: The Kim Jones x Nike Air Max 95 ‘Total Orange’ reunites the world-renowned menswear designer with the Swoosh. Twinned with an accompanying ‘Volt’ colorway, this pair features layered grey side panels in an inverted gradient finish. A black mini-Swoosh is joined by a series of perforations inspired by the Air Max 360. A translucent Nexkin overlay partially covers the sneaker’s webbing eyelets, rendered in a bold orange finish and misaligned for enhanced visual impact. The same eye-catching hue is repeated on the sneaker’s visible Max Air units. Kim Jones branding adorns the lateral heel.

results.name: Nike Air Max 90 Fried Chicken
results.story: The Nike Air Max 90 SE ‘Swoosh Mart Fried Chicken’ draws inspiration from the distinctive fried chicken packaging used by Japanese convenience stores like Family Mart. The retro runner features yellow and white stripes throughout the upper, including a tearaway outer layer on the toe box and collar. Those sections reveal orange suede paneling with assorted branding elements — including ‘Hot Air’ and ‘AM90’ — in a cartoon font. Chrome detailing lands on the sneaker’s molded eyelets, stitched-on heel patch and cropped Swoosh, while the graphic sockliner depicts a pair of metal tongs.

results.name: Nike Air Max 90 Golf Flash Lime
results.story: The Nike Air Max 90 Golf ‘Flash Lime’ reinterprets Tinker Hatfield’s classic design as a performance shoe built for the links. The streamlined upper features breathable white mesh with no-sew skins that replicate the original model’s suede overlays and leather mudguard. Fluorescent lime green detailing stands out on a Nike branded heel patch, molded eyelets and the midsole wedge, which houses a visible Max Air unit for lightweight cushioning and a smooth ride. Underfoot, the rubber outsole is equipped with flex grooves and an integrated traction pattern.

results.name: Nike Air Max 95 Kim Jones Total Volt
results.story: Developed in tandem with the celebrated menswear designer, the Kim Jones x Nike Air Max 95 ‘Volt’ updates the retro runner with refreshed details and an OG-inspired color palette. Morse code-like dots and dashes enliven side panels in charcoal grey suede, contrasted by neon pops on the sneaker’s webbing eyelets and visible Max Air units. A mini-Swoosh is added to the toe, while Kim Jones branding adorns the lateral heel. Underfoot, the translucent rubber outsole features an oversized Nike logo, with ‘KJ’ integrated into the Swoosh.

results.name: Nike Kyrie 7 Brooklyn Beats
results.story: Celebrating Brooklyn’s outsized influence within rap culture at large, the Nike Kyrie 7 ‘Brooklyn Beats’ features a boom box heel graphic and a simple white and black color scheme in honor of the hometown Nets. An unexpected pop of mint green lands on the midsole, which packs a forefoot Air Zoom Turbo unit designed to bend in every direction for enhanced on-court responsiveness. Underfoot, the rubber outsole delivers multi-directional grip via a scientifically designed traction pattern.

results.name: Kyrie 7 GS 'Hip-Hop'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Kyrie 7 GS ‘Hip-Hop’ honors the influential role that Brooklyn played in the history of rap culture. The homage is cemented with a boom box graphic embroidered on the heel, while the white and black color scheme gives the nod to the hometown Nets. The mid-top rides on a resilient foam midsole, accented with a contrasting pop of mint green on the lateral forefoot. 360-degree traction arrives via a computer-generated rubber outsole.

results.name: LeBron 18 'Home'
results.story: Celebrating LeBron James’ adopted hometown of Los Angeles, the Nike LeBron 18 ‘Home’ features a white Knitposite 2.0 upper with contrasting accents in gold and black. The latter hue is applied to the elastic collar and oversized TPU heel counter, which cradles the back of the foot for a locked-in fit. Responsive cushioning is provided by a Cushlon midsole and full-length Zoom Air unit, its back half nestled within a visible Max Air bag placed under the heel. Inside the shoe, LeBron’s jersey number is printed on the sockliner.

results.name: Zoom Freak 2 'Denim'
results.story: The Nike Zoom Freak 2 ‘Denim’ treats Giannis Antetokounmpo’s second signature shoe to a subtle makeover, highlighted by a grey textile upper and mismatched accents. The right shoe features vibrant teal branding elements that include Giannis’ personal logo on the lateral heel and an embroidered Swoosh on the medial overlay, while the left shoe is enlivened with pops of Bright Mango in the same areas. Speckled detailing is applied to a resilient foam midsole that packs Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot.

results.name: Zoom Freak 2 PS 'Denim'
results.story: Constructed for little kids, the Nike Zoom Freak 2 PS ‘Denim’ outfits Giannis Antetokounmpo’s second signature shoe with a grey textile upper. In addition to an oversized black Swoosh on the lateral side panel, the left and right shoe are enlivened with mismatched branding elements in aqua and Bright Mango accents. The low-top sits on a full-length foam midsole, dusted with speckled detailing and reinforced by a decouple rubber outsole.

results.name: Kyrie 7 EP 'Brooklyn Beats'
results.story: The Nike Kyrie 7 EP ‘Brooklyn Beats’ celebrates the link between Brooklyn and rap culture, highlighted by an embroidered heel graphic that depicts the Brooklyn Bridge atop a boom box with basketball-shaped speakers. A neutral black and white palette is applied to the sneaker’s breathable mesh upper, mounted on a foam midsole enhanced with an Air Zoom Turbo unit in the forefoot. This EP version is exclusive to Asia and features an extra-durable rubber outsole made for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Zoom Freak 2 GS 'Denim'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Zoom Freak 2 GS ‘Denim’ dresses Giannis Antetokounmpo’s second signature shoe with a grey textile upper, overlaid with white synthetic leather on the medial side and accented with mismatched aqua and Bright Mango accents. The low-top rides on a speckled foam midsole, bolstered with a molded TPU piece on the lateral sidewall for added containment and stability. Underfoot, a decoupled rubber outsole provides flexible traction.

results.name: Nike Blazer Low 77 Pine Green
results.story: The Nike Blazer Low ‘77 Vintage ‘Pine Green’ projects a simple two-tone color scheme that reflects the shoe’s hardwood origins. The white leather upper is reinforced with tonal suede overlays at the toe and lateral forefoot. Contrasting green hits make their way to the retro Swoosh and heel tab, stamped with a Nike wordmark in block lettering. A second Nike logo adorns the woven tag atop the exposed foam tongue. The low-top rides on an off-white rubber midsole that amplifies the vintage aesthetic.

results.name: Adversary Premium SB 'Turf Orange Gum Light Brown'
Air Max Plus GS 'Dark Smoke Grey'
results.colorway: Dark Smoke Grey/Light Smoke Grey/High Voltage/White

results.name: Nike Dunk Low SP Orange Pearl (PS)
results.story: Built for little kids, the Nike Dunk Low PS ‘Orange Pearl’ exhibits classic color blocking that speaks to the shoe’s college basketball roots. The pastel palette on the leather upper combines an off-white base with contrasting overlays in a delicate pink hue. Nike branding lands on the heel tab, sockliner and a woven tag atop the lightly padded nylon tongue. The low-top is mounted on a standard rubber cupsole, undergirded by a traction pattern made for pivoting on the hardwood.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Orange Pearl (W)
results.story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Orange Pearl’ offers a pastel colorway of the classic low-top, rendered in traditional color blocking in keeping with the shoe’s ‘80s roots. The upper carries a stark white base with contrasting overlays in a pale coral hue. Traditional Dunk details include a perforated toe box and a lightly padded nylon tongue marked with a woven Nike tag. The sneaker is supported by a two-tone rubber cupsole, equipped with a basketball-specific traction pattern made for pivoting.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Green Strike (W)
results.story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Green Strike’ features a color-blocked design that nods to the silhouette’s ‘80s roots. The primitive 8-bit computer graphics of that era serve as the inspiration for the sneaker’s vivid palette, which combines a white leather base with a yellow forefoot overlay, lime green Swoosh, crimson eyestay and periwinkle heel. Contrasting black hits make their way to the woven tongue tag and heel tab, both marked with classic Nike branding.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low SP Orange Pearl (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘Orange Pearl’ outfits a scaled-down version of the iconic silhouette in a leather upper with classic two-tone color blocking. An off-white base is contrasted by a subtle pastel finish on the Swoosh, heel tab and forefoot and heel overlays. A soft nylon mesh tongue combines with a padded textile collar to deliver a comfortable fit for little feet. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features the same grippy tread used on the OG ‘80s high-top.

results.name: Force Zoom Trout 7 Pro Mid 'Game Royal'
Air Zoom Infinity Tour NRG 'The Players Championship'
Cosmic Unity 'Space Hippie'
results.story: The Nike Cosmic Unity ‘Space Hippie’ dresses the hoops shoe in the cool hues that distinguish the brand’s eco-friendly footwear line, which marries radical design and repurposed ‘space junk.’ The sneaker’s breathable textile upper, constructed from recycled cable yarn, is mounted on a Crater Foam midsole that uses a blend proprietary foams and around 10% Nike Grind. A sockliner made with recycled content sits directly atop a full-length Zoom Air Strobel, stripped of binding material and formed in part with recycled TPU.

results.name: Nike Air Max 90 St Patricks Day (2021)
results.story: The Nike Air Max 90 ‘St. Patrick’s Day’ prepares for March 17 with a suitably festive palette that incorporates two different shades of green. The upper is constructed from breathable white mesh with leather overlays in Pine Green, including the shamrock-embossed mudguard. Mean Green accents land on the sneaker’s anterior eyelets, Nike branded heel patch and polyurethane midsole, featuring signature Air sole cushioning under the heel.

results.name: Cosmic Unity EP 'Space Hippie'
results.story: The Nike Cosmic Unity EP ‘Space Hippie’ weds basketball performance capabilities with a sustainable build directly inspired by the brand’s exploratory footwear collection, one that imagines the scarcity of materials that accompanies life on Mars. Recycled materials are incorporated into virtually all aspects of the shoe, including the Crater Foam midsole and full-length Zoom Air Strobel, partially constructed from recycled TPU and stitched directly onto the layered textile upper. This EP version is exclusive to Asia and sports an extra-durable rubber outsole made for outdoor courts.

results.name: LeBron 18 Low 'Bred'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 Low ‘Bred’ combines a low-profile build with an essential color scheme virtually synonymous with Nike heritage. Black woven textile is utilized on the upper, fortified with a series of tonal no-sew overlays and an external heel clip that locks in the back of the foot. Contrasting red accents atop the tongue include LeBron James’ embroidered signature. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a React foam midsole, supplemented by a crimson-tinged Max Air unit under the heel.

results.name: Wmns ZoomX Invincible Run Flyknit 'Black Elemental Pink'
Wmns ZoomX Invincible Run Flyknit 'Black White'
ZoomX Invincible Run Flyknit 'Black Chile Red'
Alpha Huarache Elite 3 Low 'White Light Smoke Grey'
Air Force 1 '07 'Contrast Stitch - White Laser Orange'
Nike Overbreak SP Undercover Black
results.story: The Undercover x Nike Overbreak SP ‘Black’ draws from design concepts introduced in the Japanese brand’s Spring/Summer 2021 collection. The sneaker makes use of a black textile upper, accented with a metallic silver Swoosh and an embroidered red rose graphic on the lateral quarter panel. Tonal synthetic suede overlays reinforce the heel and forefoot, the latter featuring ‘Chaos’ and ‘Balance’ printed atop the right and left shoe. Speckled detailing is dusted on a molded React foam midsole that recalls the Nike Overreact.

results.name: Nike Overbreak SP Undercover Sail
results.story: The Undercover x Nike Overbreak SP ‘Overcast’ blends heritage track style with hyper-modern tooling and a fashion-forward aesthetic in keeping with Jun Takahashi’s design vision. An embroidered red rose decorates the cream-hued textile upper, fortified with tonal synthetic suede overlays and a textured Kurim eyestay. ‘Chaos’ and ‘Balance’ are inscribed on the toe box of the right and left shoe, while Undercover Jun Takahashi is stamped on the black leather heel tab. The sneaker’s distinctively molded React foam midsole is borrowed from the Nike Overreact.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Syracuse (W) (2021)
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Nike women’s Dunk High SP ‘Syracuse’ brings back one of the original colorways of the brand’s iconic ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985. The leather high-top is dressed in the signature colors of Syracuse University, featuring a white base with contrasting overlays in Orange Blaze. The citrus hue is repeated on the Swoosh and woven tongue tag, as well as a rubber outsole originally developed for the collegiate hardwood.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Syracuse (2021)
results.story: The 2021 iteration of the Nike Dunk High SP ‘Syracuse’ brings back one of the OG colorways of the ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985. The leather high-top is rendered in the signature hues of Syracuse University, featuring a crisp white base with contrasting Orange Blaze overlays. Classic Nike branding makes its way to a woven tag atop a lightly padded nylon mesh tongue. The high-top rides on a rubber cupsole, finished in the same two-tone color scheme utilized on the upper.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low White Black (2021) (W)
results.story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Black White’ highlights classic color blocking on a vintage silhouette originally released in 1985. The all-leather upper features a crisp white base with contrasting black overlays and a matching black Swoosh. Nike branding lands on the heel tab and woven tongue tag in keeping with the sneaker’s OG aesthetic. The low-top is supported by a durable rubber cupsole, equipped underfoot with a basketball-specific traction pattern.

results.name: Nike Dunk High SP Syracuse (GS) (2021)
results.story: One of the original colorways from the ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985, the Nike Dunk High SP GS ‘Syracuse’ returns in OG form in 2021. The leather upper features a clean white base with contrasting overlays in Orange Blaze. A padded high-cut collar combines with a breathable mesh tongue to deliver a comfortable fit. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a traction pattern nearly identical to another heritage basketball shoe released in 1985 — the Air Jordan 1.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘Black White’ offers a scaled-down version of the retro hoops shoe for little feet, rendered in an elemental two-tone color scheme that spans both the leather upper and tooling. Design details remain faithful to Peter Moore’s original 1985 silhouette, highlighted by a woven Nike tag atop a lightly padded nylon tongue. The rubber outsole, featuring a traction pattern the Dunk shares with the Air Jordan 1, offers superior grip.

results.name: Wmns Air Max 270 'White Pink Blast Volt'
Air Max 270 Extreme GS 'Pure Platinum Blue Void'
Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (2021)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Black White’ treats the retro model to an essential two-tone color scheme that accentuates the sneaker’s clean lines, developed by designer Peter Moore and responsible for the shoe’s easy transition from the hardwood to the street. The leather upper combines a white base with contrasting black overlays that wrap around the toe and heel. On both the woven tongue tag and heel tab, Nike branding in white stands out in relief against a black backdrop.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (PS)
results.story: Made for little kids, the Nike Dunk Low PS ‘Black White’ offers an elemental colorway of the vintage silhouette originally designed for the hardwood. The leather upper combines a crisp white base with contrasting black overlays and a matching black Swoosh. Cushioned comfort and ease of movement are made possible by a padded collar and nylon mesh tongue, the latter decorated with a woven Nike tag for branding that stays true to the shoe’s ‘80s roots.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS)
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low GS ‘Black White’ showcases a simplistic two-tone color scheme that accentuates the sneaker’s clean lines, born from the same designer — Peter Moore — that also created the Air Jordan 1. The low-top’s leather upper, combining a white base with starkly contrasting overlays in basic black, rides on a low-profile midsole. Underfoot, the rubber outsole is equipped with a traction pattern specifically designed for quick pivots on the hardwood.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Syracuse (2021) (PS)
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Nike Dunk High SP PS 'Syracuse’ revives one of the original colorways of the iconic ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985. Dressed in the signature colors of Syracuse University, the high-top carries a white leather upper with contrasting orange leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. Additional citrus accents land on the sneaker’s branding elements, including the woven tongue tag and signature Swoosh. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a pivot-point traction pattern originally designed for the hardwood.

results.name: Kyrie 7 'Chinese New Year'
results.story: The Kyrie 7 ‘Chinese New Year’ updates Kyrie Irving’s seventh signature shoe with a celebratory colorway inspired by the lunar holiday. The design focus is centered around the Chinese knot, signifying prosperity and good fortune. In addition to a knotted gold Swoosh on the lateral quarter panel, the black heel overlay is embellished with an additional gold Swoosh and an intricate knot in a traditional red hue. A contrasting pop pf turquoise lands on the Phylon midsole, which houses a forefoot Air Zoom Turbo unit for ultra-responsive cushioning.

results.name: MD Valiant TD 'Dark Smoke Grey Sunset Pulse'
Air Max 2090 GS 'Topography'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Air Max 2090 GS ‘Topography’ presents a simplistic two-tone colorway of the lifestyle runner that takes its cues from the classic Air Max 90 silhouette. Carried over from the older shoe are a cropped Swoosh, molded heel patch and leather mudguard, embellished with multiple Swooshes and wavy lines that mimic the look of a topographic map. The sneaker rides on a soft foam midsole, its solid black sidewalls offset by a red-tinged Max Air unit under the heel.

results.name: NikeCourt Air Zoom Vapor Cage 4 'Obsidian Copa'
Wmns TC 7900 'Black Ghost Green'
results.story: The Nike women’s TC 7900 ‘Black Ghost Green’ showcases neon accents on a chunky lifestyle silhouette built for everyday wear. A tonal black finish is executed on the layered leather upper, equipped with decorative webbing straps around the midfoot and toe box for a utilitarian aesthetic. Dual pull tabs assist with easy on and off, while mesh construction on the tongue and collar improves the shoe’s breathability quotient. Plush cushioning is provided by an exaggerated foam midsole in a fluorescent green hue.

results.name: NikeCourt Zoom Vapor Cage 4 Rafa 'Football Grey Green Glow'
Wmns Air Force 1 Shadow 'White Solar Red'
results.story: The Nike women’s Air Force 1 Shadow ‘White Solar Red’ treats the classic silhouette to a reconstructed build with layered detailing. The sneaker’s white leather upper is equipped with doubled-up eyestays and forefoot overlays, along with a detached collar flap and a stitched-on Air-branded overlay that wraps around the heel. The latter is rendered in bright red and dark teal, matching the double-stacked Swooshes and heel tabs. A cored-out rubber outsole completes the modern aesthetic.

results.name: Nike Dunk High SE All-Star (2021)
results.story: Celebrating the NBA’s midseason break, the Nike Dunk High ‘All Star 2021’ delivers an eye-catching two-tone colorway of the retro hoops shoe. The upper combines a pistachio-hued leather base with contrasting patent leather overlays in a glossy black finish. A standard Nike woven tag decorates the tongue, while an NBA All-Star emblem is stitched onto the lateral heel. The high-top is mounted on a standard rubber cupsole, featuring a pivot-ready traction pattern originally designed for the hardwood.

results.name: ZoomX SuperRep Surge 'Smoke Grey Light Blue Fury'
results.colorway: Light Smoke Grey/Light Blue Fury/White/University Red

results.name: Wmns Venture Runner 'Black Light Arctic Pink'
results.story: Inspired by classic running shoes from the ‘80s, the Nike women’s Venture Runner ‘Black Light Arctic Pink’ steps out in a traditional mesh and suede upper. Contemporary touches include an oversized pink Swoosh, double layered eyelets and exposed zigzag stitching on the quarter panel. In addition to Nike branding on the woven tongue tag, ‘Nike Sportswear’ is embossed on the external heel clip. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a modified waffle tread as a tie-in to the brand’s running heritage.

results.name: Air Max 270 TD 'Light Smoke Grey Crimson'
results.colorway: Light Smoke Grey/Dark Smoke Grey/Bright Crimson/White

results.name: Air Max 270 Extreme TD 'Dark Smoke Grey Bright Crimson'
Wmns Air Max 2090 'White Siren Red'
results.story: The Nike women’s Air Max 2090 ‘White Siren Red’ delivers a clean colorway of a lifestyle silhouette inspired by the iconic Air Max 90. A speed lacing system secures the semi-translucent textile upper, finished in a subtle off-white shade and reinforced with a tonal leather mudguard. The sneaker’s open-hole tongue combines with a pull tab at the heel for easy on and off. The lightweight build is mounted on a soft foam midsole, fitted with a crimson-tinged Max Air unit in the heel and supported by a waffle-tread rubber outsole.
